<head>
<title>Come Visit The Institute</title>
</head>

<body>

<center>
<h2>Come Visit The Institute</h2>
</center>

No trip to Washington, would be complete without a visit to theLeadership Intitute. And visitors are welcome to stop by at any time.<p>

Supporters are invited to visit the current Institute offices in Springfield, Virginia, just outside the Washington beltway.<p>

President Morton Blackwell enjoys conducting tours and most often serves as guide.<p>

Come see the staff in action as they recruit activists and make plans for the many tnaining schools.<p>

Feel free to chat with the Institlute interns about their experiences.  A visit to the Sacher Intern House can also be arranged to get a feel for the whole intern experience.<p>

Special tours are also available to see the new building purchased in November, now under renovation and constsuction.<p>

Please keep this invitation in mind. Morton Blackwell's assistant, Amy Green, keeps his schedule. Don't hesitate to call her at (703) 247-2000 and let her know when you can visit.<p><p>

