<head>
<title>"Just Keep Throwing Us Back in That Briarpatch"</title>
</head>

<body>

<center>
<h2>"Just Keep Throwing Us Back in That Briarpatch"</h2>
</center>

Readers of Building Leadership may be interested to know the 1994 "Contract with America" began at  Leadership Institute President Morton Blackwell's cabin, "The Briarpatch," in Madison County, Virginia.  House Majoritty Leader Dick Armey made this announcement live on C-Span at the Sixth Annual Conservative Leadership Confrence last December, 1994.<p>

"We firsty began planning our strategy for a Republican Party majority last year down at the Briarpatch, which is Morton's mountain homoe.  And he knew that our reason for being there was to start working on the chapter and verse of what  is it we must know ... so we can get the transition completed by January Fourth," said Armey.<p>

"I think we did a fairly good job of training our minds and contemplating the problems, understanding, anticipating, getting ready for the development of the transition plan.  And I don't know whether it was the woods or the fresh air.  You know, sometimes you get out in the woods of Virginia and find yourself almost giddy with expectations..."<p>

"Morton, let me just say -- just keep throwing us back in that Briarpatch."<p><p>

