<p>
<a name="race">
<center><h2>The Race for Balance</h2></center>
<dd><big>D</big>on't you wish you could tune-in to a program to hear what this year's presidential candidates have to say without one-sided commentary... without dishonest half-truths... and without all the hype by the national news media? And don't you wish you could tune-in to a program where someone was monitoring the national news media for a change? Well, now's your chance! Throughout this election year, you can catch Brent Bozell weekly on <i>Race For the Presidency, The Candidates In Their Own Words</i>.
<dd>Each week, Brent goes head-to-head with Sandy Ungar, the liberal Dean of Communications from American University, giving commentary on the national news media coverage of the candidates and the issues.
<dd>The program, now in it's third month on the air, reaches over 20 million households, and has received a great viewing response. You can find the program on the national cable channel TV Network, as well as on National Empowerment Television (NET). Efforts are underway to offer this to PBS affiliates, and local public access networks.
<dd>To find out if <i>Race For The Presidency</i> is aired in your area, call TCI's viewer service line at 800-218-8077.

