<P><LI>  "`Precious Ground' Lost As More Youths Turn On,"<I> Sun-Sentinel</I>, December 13, 1994, p. A-1.
<P><LI>  "National Survey Finds Teen Drug Use Up," op. cit.
<P><LI> "Survey of State Prison Inmates, 1991," Bureau of Justice Statistics, U.S. Department of Justice, 
March 1993, NCJ-136949, p. 21.
<P><LI> Matt Schofield, "`Wilding' Slaying Shocks Dodge City,"<I> Kansas City Star</I>, May 3, 1991.
<P><LI> "Teenager Says Burning Man Was `Big Game,'"<I> New York Times</I>, August 29, 1993, p. A-15.
<P><LI> Larry Oakes, "Although Crime Was Horrifying, Woman Stood by Her Grandson," <I>Star Tribune</I>, November 7, 1987.
<P><LI>  Trish Power, "Suspect Distraught After Fatal Shooting,"<I> The Herald</I>, May 3, 1994.
<P><LI> J. Fagan et al., "Delinquency and Substance Use Among Inner-City Students,"<I> Journal of Drug 
Issues</I>, Vol. 20, No. 3, pp. 351-399.
<P><LI>  R. Akers, "Delinquent Behavior, Drugs, and Alcohol: What Is the Relationship?,"<I> Today's 
Delinquent</I>, Vol. 3, 1984, pp. 19-48; L. S. Wright, "High School Polydrug Users and Abusers," 
<I>Adolescence</I>, Vol. 20, No. 80, pp. 853-861.
<P><LI>  Donna E. Shalala, op. cit.
<P><LI>  Jordana Hart, "Drugs Embedded in Teen-Age Culture,"<I> The Boston Globe</I>, December 14, 1994.
<P><LI>  Ibid.
<P><LI>  Dennis Cauchon, "High Times Return,"<I> USA Today</I>, March 19, 1993, p. D-2.
<P><LI>  Christopher John Farley, "Hello Again, Mary Jane," CWD International Newsletter, 1993.
<P><LI>  Roger Catlin, "Pot Makes Comeback in Rock Music," <I>The Hartford Courant</I>, March 12, 1993, p. 
A-1.
<P><LI> Ibid.
<P><LI>  Chris Mundy, "Green Days,"<I> Rolling Stone</I>, January 26, 1995, pp 44 & 46.
<P><LI>  Cited in Thomas L. Jipping, "Heavy Metal, Rap, and America's Youth: Issues and Alternatives," A 
Special Report of the Free Congress Foundation, 1990; <I>Implications</I>, Vol. 4, Nos. 1 and 2, Summer 
1991, p. 2.
<P><LI>  Cited in Jipping, op. cit., p. 11.
<P><LI>  Cited in Jipping, op. cit., p.3; Robert Demski, "Music, Advertising, and Teenagers,"<I> American 
