88.
<P><LI> Cited in Jipping, op. cit.; Avram Goldstein, "Thrills in Response to Music and Other Stimuli," 
<I>Physiological Psychology</I>, 1980, pp. 126-129.
<P><LI> Cited in Jipping, op. cit., p. 12; "Mrs. Gore's Advice to Parents Carries a Parental Advisory," 
<I>Memphis Commercial Appeal</I>, April 18, 1987.
<P><LI> Douglas MacKinnon, "Too Weak To Say No,"<I> The Washington Post</I>, January 28, 1995, p. A-13.
<P><LI> Elizabeth F. Brown and William R. Hendee, "Adolescents and Their Music: Insights into the 
Health of Adolescents," <I>Journal of the American Medical Association</I>, September 22, 1989, p. 1661.
<P><LI>  Schultze, op. cit., p. 204.
<P><LI>  "The Sayings of Chairman Bob," in Schultze, op. cit., p. 192.
<P><LI>  Dennis Cooper, op. cit., p. 106.
<P><LI>  Ibid.
<P><LI> Ibid.
<P><LI>  Ibid.
<P><LI>  Dennis Cooper, op. cit.
<P><LI>  Jordana Hart, op. cit.
<P><LI>  Dennis Cooper, op. cit.
<P><LI>  "School Supplies for the '90s," MTV Community of the Future, 1515 Broadway, 23rd Floor, New 
York, NY.
<P><LI> "Money Talks: The Lowdown on Dollars and Since,"<I> Details</I>, March 1995, p. 56.
<P><LI> <I> Rolling Stone</I>, October 20, 1994, p. 162.
<P><LI> <I> Rolling Stone</I>, December 12, 1994, p. 208.
<P><LI> <I> Q</I>, February 1995, p. 142.
